statistics when we go through the specific tests.","position":{"start":{"line":72,"column":1},"end":{"line":72,"column":1}},"key":"uKnSx0aRQ7"}],"key":"fWHb1QLg75"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":74,"column":1},"end":{"line":74,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":74,"column":1},"end":{"line":74,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Hypothesis testing step 3: Assessing the evidence.","position":{"start":{"line":74,"column":1},"end":{"line":74,"column":1}},"key":"uZXMJjgrYF"}],"key":"LY3hyyvvk8"}],"key":"uFBV4Ti1c0"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"As we saw, this is the step where we calculate how likely is it to get data like that observed when H~o~ true. In a sense, this is the heart of the process, since we draw our conclusions based on this probability. If this probability is very small (see example 2), then that means that it would be very surprising to get data like that observed if H~0~ were true. The fact that we ","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"FNGdOiY4uF"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"did","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"HfWYDmWAuI"}],"key":"gdi7A54r67"},{"type":"text","value":" observe such data is therefore evidence against H~0~, and we should reject it. On the other hand, if this probability is not very small (see example 3) this means that observing data like that observed is not very surprising if H~0~ were true, so the fact that we observed such data does not provide evidence against H~o~. This crucial probability, therefore, has a special name. It is called the ","position":{"start":{"line":76,"column":1},"end":{"line":76,"column":1}},"key":"PFU2hvUnew"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line"